  "text": "ATRA plus Chemotherapy. Very soon, after the experience of the Shangai group, ATRA was combined with anthracycline-based chemotherapies. The concurrent administration of ATRA plus cytotoxic chemotherapies produced a complete remission (CR) rate in more than 80 percent of patients of all ages with newly diagnosed APL [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] and almost all treatment failures were due to early mortality, 21 whereas primary resistance to the combination of ATRA and chemotherapy was unusual except for patients with the rare t(11;17) who must generally be treated as the other AML.",
